When Francesco Totti made his debut for Roma in 1993, few could have predicted that he’d spend the next 25 years at the club. The Italian made the first of 786 appearances for Roma on March 28, 1993, when he came off the bench in a 2-0 win at Brescia. The goals came from Claudio Caniggia and Sinisa Mihajlovic with a trademark free-kick, and we’ve revisited that day to look back at the starting XI who got to share with Totti what we now know to be a landmark day. Read the full article here. The post Where are they now? The Roma starting XI for Totti’s debut appeared first on Football365. Source: Football 365 First name * Email * Phone Number  Check your inbox or spam folder to confirm your subscription. Former Italy international Francesco Totti has confirmed his retirement from professional football. Totti, 40, who made the announcement in an interview on Roma's official website on Monday, is expected to take up a director's role with the Rome-based club. "The end of my playing career was May 28, 2017. That for… July 17, 2017 In "Sports" Francesco Totti says leaving Roma after 30 years is “like dying” after he resigned from his role as a director at the Serie A club. The World Cup winner, 42, spent his entire professional career at Roma and retired from playing in July 2017. His relationship with president James Pallotta… June 18, 2019 In "News" Former Italy striker Francesco Totti on Thursday said accepting the end of a legendary footballing career was tough. Totti He told newsmen that “at the beginning, I was talking to myself like a madman, I’m injured, I’m suspended, I’ll be back in a kit soon, though I’ve got used to… November 30, 2017 In "News"